@page
@model NekoWiki.Pages.Archive.ragdollModel
@{
    <style>
        body {
            background-image: url('/img/background.png');
            background-size: 100% auto;
            background-repeat: repeat;
            background-attachment: fixed;
            background-position: center top;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
        }

        .content-block::after {
            content: "";
            display: table;
            clear: both;
        }
    </style>

    <div class="container-flex">
        <div class="content-block" style="max-width: 900px;
                                     margin: 20px auto;
                                     padding: 20px;
                                     border: 1px solid #ccc;
                                     overflow: auto;
                                     background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.85);
                                     border-radius: 10px;
                                     box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);">

            <img src="~/img/cats/ragdoll.png" alt="ragdoll"
                 style="float: right;
                            margin-left: 20px;
                            margin-bottom: 10px;
                            width: 300px;
                            height: 300px;
                            object-fit: cover;
                            border-radius: 8px;">

            <h1>Ragdoll Cat</h1>
            <p>The Ragdoll is a large, semi-longhaired cat breed famous for its striking blue eyes and tendency to completely relax and go limp like a rag doll when held (hence the name). They are known for their gentle, dog-like temperament.</p>

            <h2>Origin:</h2>
            <p>The breed originated in the 1960s in California, USA, developed by breeder Ann Baker. The breed's foundation stock included a white, longhaired female named Josephine. Ragdolls are highly valued for their sweet disposition and plush appearance.</p>

            <h2>Character and features</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Size: Large, muscular, and heavy-boned. They mature slowly, often reaching full size around four years of age. Males can weigh between 6–9 kg.</li>
                <li>Coat: Semi-long, silky, and dense, without a thick undercoat, which means less matting than some other longhaired breeds. They have color points similar to the Siamese.</li>
                <li>Temperament: Extremely affectionate, docile, and placid. They are highly social, playful, and often follow their owners around the house. They are non-aggressive and excellent with children.</li>
                <li>Distinguishing Traits: Bright, deep blue eyes; a soft, rabbit-like coat; and the unique ability to relax completely when picked up.</li>
            </ul>

        </div>
    </div>
}
